Plotting from SWATH tsv input files

Missed Cleavages

For each sequence, OpenSwathWorkflow does an in situ digest (assuming Trypsin) and places the number of missed cleavages for each peptide in a column 'MC'. This columns can currently only be found in the tsv output from OpenSwathWorkflow, so this plot will only be available if swath tsv file(s) were provided.
Processing data: all peptides tagged as decoys are dropped before plotting and transitions groups are groupedso that each peptide is counted only once.
QC target: sample preparation

ID over RT

This histogram shows the number of Identifications made in each retention time interval. In this plot, each bar represents a 5 minute interval, the actual retention time is displayed in seconds on the x axis.
These plots can be generated from OpenSwathWorkflow output files, that can be either in either in tsv or osw fromat. In this case, tsv files were used. For each given input file a subplot is generated
Please compare runs and make sure, the number of IDs are stable over RT dimension and between runs

PeakWidth over RT

This plot shows the variation of peak width over the RT dimension.
The data for these plots was taken from OpenSwathWorkflow output in tsv format. Peak Width is calculated from the leftWidth and rightWidth columns. RT was grouped into 5 minute time interval and a boxplot for each time interval show the mean peak width and the variation of the data

Correlation with Library Intensity

The correlation of assay library (DDA) intensity with DIA intensity is calculated by OpenSwathWorkflow as one of many sub-scores, that describe describe the peak group. This score is plotted here as boxplot for each provided swath tsv file.

Mean Mass Error

PeakWidth over RT

This plot shows the variation of peak width over the RT dimension.
The data for these plots was taken from OpenSwathWorkflow output in tsv format. Peak Width is calculated from the leftWidth and rightWidth columns. RT was grouped into 5 minute time interval and a boxplot for each time interval show the mean peak width and the variation of the data

Number of transitions

Each Transitions group (peptide) might get identified multiple times during a run. This histogram shows the distribution, of how often peptides were identified.
This plot is only available from tsv

Library Coverage

Venn diagram of library coverage. This can only be plotted if the library assay list was provided in tsv format. Libraries in pqp format are currently not supported.
Library coverage wil be plotted from tsv files, if they were provided, otherwise it can also be plotted from osw files.
Coverage of the merged file from pyprophet is inlcuded and will be plotted from tsv first, if bothe were provided.
